# .cursorrules - WC26 Hybrid Analytics v3.1
# Do not override without explicit human approval.

## PACKAGE MANAGER
- Always use pnpm. Never use npm or yarn.
- Never commit package-lock.json or yarn.lock.

## CODE PARADIGMS
- Prefer React Server Components by default.
- Use "use client" only when browser APIs or interactivity require it.
- Use Server Actions for ALL data mutations and fetches.
- No useEffect for data fetching.
- No global state libraries (Redux, Zustand).

## DUAL-MODE ISOLATION
- components/global and components/bluelock must never import from each other.
- lib/ml/global and lib/ml/bluelock are fully isolated.
- Blue Lock mode applies to FW position players only.
- FIFA/EA ratings are banned from all ML pipelines.

## FILE EDITING
- Never modify more than 5 files per change.
- No global refactors without explicit approval.

## ML RULES
- All ML runs in Python scripts under /scripts/. Never in Next.js.
- Grade bands defined only in config/ml-bluelock.ts and lib/ml/bluelock/grades.ts.
- creativity_score is a primary feature in: BL Pass category, Ego Freedom axis, Global Chance Creation.

## TYPESCRIPT
- Strict mode ON. No `any` without explanatory comment.
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for data shapes.

## GIT
- Commit format: slice(N): description
- Never commit .env.local or real keys.
- Run pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck before every commit.
